description: This all-new book follows the adventures of IT as he leaves his boring life to explore and destroy all new realms. Bored with a life spent beating an endless supply of kittens, IT ventures outside and discovers a world entirely new to him. Though he is at first elated to find a place full of wonder and happiness, IT soon realizes that he can never belong. IT is depressed until he realizes that, even in this strange new world, everything can be beaten.

Features an illustrated retelling of one of the most pivitol battles in the American Civil War. Includes historical photos from the Civil War, maps, and a who's who run down on the major players. This is a great learning tool and will help anyone, young or old, get caught up on their American History.

Presenting another great new talent, this time from Scotland, in a retro story of bondage with some fairies. Full of stylish deviance and Victorian proper facade whilst the scene behind is pervy to the exquisite max! Emilys Aunt gives her a secret brooch which wakes up her nascent sexuality and her aunt has very delicious plans to accomodate!
name: GN
Erstes Buch: Das Kind des Tierkreises

description: As Halloween approaches we found our creepiest, funniest - and scariest - excerpt from the pages of Bone! As Fone Bone, Gran'ma and Thorn make their journey to Atheia, they have an unexpected encounter with the two stupid Rat Creatures - and a bloody battle ensues! Things are bound to get worse as the mighty Kingdok arrives on the scene, ready to shred Gran'ma to bits. This is an excerpt from Bone #21, which appears in full in the color graphic novel: The Dragonslayer from Scholastic/Graphix, and in B&W in Bone: One Volume Edition from Cartoon Books!

A spooky excerpt from the climactic final chapter of the Bone series, just in time for Halloween! Fone Bone follows after Thorn as he makes his way through the dangerous dragon burial ground that leads to the Crown of Horns, and elsewhere, Gran'ma Ben and Phoney Bone are trapped by The Hooded One and her army of rat creatures! Each must overcome their most feared enemies to stop the Lord of the Locust's return!
Initially published periodically in the Belgian daily La Dernire Heure from January 16 2008 onwards before being collected as an album by Les Editions Blake Et Mortimer later the same year.
name: Le Sanctuaire du Gondwana

description:
The Mayan God of the Underworld, Bolon Yokte Ku, is at his strongest when the star Sagittarius A is aligned with the center of our galaxy (also known as the Dark Rift). This happens every 5,000 years, and this alignment is occurring right now in the year 2012.

Aided by a giant, mythological puma made of stone, K'u intends to network the Valley of the Volcanoes (in ) with the molten rivers of Xibilba (Mayan Hell), and erupt them all at once. This will ruin the atmosphere of the planet, causing plants, animals and even humans to expire.

5,000 years ago in Central America, Ku tried this same ploy. But a Mesoamerican Creation God, Viracocha, stopped him. After being contacted by William Aether (the ESOU psychic), Viracocha has agreed to help the ESOU because the puma aiding Ku is actually a creation of Viracochas. However, Viracocha lacks followers and is weak compared to the God that was able to stop Ku years ago. Unruffled, Ku is ready for his vision to become a reality, a new beginning...for a DARK WORLD.
name: Transmission of Will

description:
Rincewind the "Wizzard" lives in the city of fair Ankh-Morpork, a metropolis placed atop the Discworld, a flat earth being carried through space on the backs of four giant elephants, who in turn rest on the back of an even more gigantic celestial turtle, the Great A'Tuin. A failed mage, Rincewind only wants to have a peaceful and unexciting life. So it is extremely unfortunate for him when he runs into the Discworld's first tourist, Twoflower, come sightseeing to Ankh-Morpork from the fabled, and often believed to be mythical, Agatean Empire, accompanied by his homicidally sentient Luggage. As one of the few people able to communicate with Twoflower in a language the tourist understands, the extremely reluctant Rincewind finds himself forced to become Twoflower's guide by Ankh-Morpork's ruler, the Patrician, who fears the Agatean Emperor's wrath should something untoward befall a citizen of that empire within the bounds of crime-ridden Ankh-Morpork. Unfortunately for the city, Twoflower works in "inn sewers ants", and once he explains the concept of people agreeing to pay out if you make a bet with them that your business won't burn down, he inspires the first attempt at insurance fraud on the Disc.

As a result, the unlikely companions are forced to flee the burning city, and venture into the wilds beyond. Out of the frying pan, and into the fire...

When last seen, the cowardly failed wizard Rincewind and Discworld's first tourist Twoflower were falling off the edge of the disc and into outer space. Can things possibly get worse for our unlikely heroes?

Yes. Yes, they can.
name: The Light Fantastic

description: Great A'Tuin, the celestial turtle that carries the four elephants who in turn carry the Discworld on their backs, is swimming through space towards a giant red sun, apparently dooming the Disc to imminent destruction. Doomsday cults are springing up on the Disc, and the only chance this unlikely flat world has for survival rests with the unlikely band consisting of the cowardly and inept failed wizard Rincwind, his naive tourist companion Twoflower, the world's oldest and most toothless barbarian Cohen, and a charmingly homicidal animated chest, the Luggage.

person_credits.name: Jack T. Chick

description: Death comes to all men in time. When he came to Mort, he offered him a job. And so Mort becomes Death's apprentice, taking a career path he could never have anticipated, especially when Death decides to take a holiday, leaving Mort stuck with Death's job, Death's grump manservant Albert, Death's psychopathic adopted daughter Ysabell, and in way over his head!

description: From the mind of Andy Riley, creator of The Book Of Bunny Suicides, comes another collection of blackly comic cartoon strips. As the title suggests, this volume takes a mischievous look at parenting.

volume.name: Great Lies To Tell Small Kids
